page.title: 14WILDLIFE IN EAST MERSEA
page.content: A wildlife survey in June at Cudmore Grove Country Park obtained the following results. {BIRDS:}The following species were identified;Kestrels hovering and Carrion Crows nesting in the trees; Linnets,Chaffinches,Sparrows and Whitethroats near the carpark; Woodpigeons and Blackbirds in the Ranger's garden;Coots,Moorhens and Swans in the pond and dyke;Kittiwakes and Black-headed Gulls near the beach;Swallows,Sparrows and Skylarks were found generally in the park. { MAMMALS:}Only Rabbits were seen. {INSECTS:}Caterpillars,Bees,Cuckoo Spit,Gnats,Spiders,Flies,Butterflies including Painted Ladies and Cabbage Whites and Ladybirds were found around the park.
